From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: JohnOS <noreply@example.com>
Date: Mon, 23 Mar 2026 12:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] ffmpeg8: relax v4l2-request configure gate for older kernel
 headers

FFmpeg 8 in nixpkgs is currently built against kernel headers that do not
define the newer M2M hold-capture-buffer flag used by the V4L2 request decode
helpers.

The request decoder already contains a runtime fallback that queues each slice
as a full frame when hold-capture is not supported by the driver, so this
feature must not be a configure-time hard requirement.
---
 configure | 3 +--
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 2 deletions(-)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 99f9f0d8f61e7..8caab86b4da10 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -3202 +3202 @@
-v4l2_request_deps="linux_media_h v4l2_timeval_to_ns v4l2_m2m_hold_capture_buf libdrm libudev"
+v4l2_request_deps="linux_media_h v4l2_timeval_to_ns libdrm libudev"
@@ -7380,7 +7380,6 @@ if enabled v4l2_request; then
     check_cc h264_v4l2_request linux/videodev2.h "int i = V4L2_CID_STATELESS_H264_DECODE_MODE"
     check_cc hevc_v4l2_request linux/videodev2.h "int i = V4L2_CID_STATELESS_HEVC_SPS"
     check_cc mpeg2_v4l2_request linux/videodev2.h "int i = V4L2_CID_STATELESS_MPEG2_SEQUENCE"
-    check_cc v4l2_m2m_hold_capture_buf linux/videodev2.h "int i = V4L2_BUF_FLAG_M2M_HOLD_CAPTURE_BUF"
     check_func_headers "linux/media.h linux/videodev2.h" v4l2_timeval_to_ns
     check_pkg_config libudev libudev libudev.h udev_new
     check_struct linux/videodev2.h "struct v4l2_ctrl_hevc_decode_params" num_delta_pocs_of_ref_rps_idx
-- 
2.49.0
